 cheap flash device normally just kills the devic :-(.<br /><br />Not my experience. It may be true for some really cheap devices, but<br />normal USB keys seem to just get really slow, probably due to having<br />had their flash rewrite algorithm tuned for FAT accesses.<br /><br />I *do* suspect that to see the really bad behavior, you don't write<br />just one large file to it, but many smaller ones. "git clone" will<br />check out all the kernel tree files, obviously.<br /><br />                     Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
